664
00:50:35,796 --> 00:50:38,417
That was somewhat of a lengthy process that took place.

665
00:50:39,618 --> 00:50:43,460
I believe there was much division in the community over this process.

666
00:50:44,120 --> 00:50:47,222
Many people felt that they weren't heard.

667
00:50:47,282 --> 00:50:49,403
Many people felt that they weren't part of the process.

668
00:50:50,283 --> 00:51:02,389
And what I'm offering here tonight, Mr. President, is that we take a closer look at the naming of any building in the community, whether it's on the school side or the city side.

669
00:51:03,369 --> 00:51:04,570
As a member of the school committee,

670
00:51:05,337 --> 00:51:06,958
I can attest to you firsthand.

671
00:51:07,598 --> 00:51:16,381
I actually am one of the members that actually voted against the naming of one of our schools back some 20 years ago.

672
00:51:17,261 --> 00:51:20,082
And it wasn't because I was opposed to the name, Mr. President.

673
00:51:20,502 --> 00:51:22,663
It was more of a process issue I had.

674
00:51:23,383 --> 00:51:25,924
And at the time, I felt there wasn't enough public input.

675
00:51:26,685 --> 00:51:30,726
There wasn't enough community participation in regards to the selection of the name.

676
00:51:31,326 --> 00:51:33,227
And therefore, I actually voted against

677
00:51:33,951 --> 00:51:38,815
the naming of one of our, what we refer to as new schools now that are 20 years old.

678
00:51:39,736 --> 00:51:59,072
I would say, Mr. President, that in a community of this size, when you're talking about naming a school building, and know that many of these buildings, whether it's a municipal building, or a park, or the corner of an intersection that's named, this has personal memories to people.

679
00:51:59,573 --> 00:52:02,215
It has personal feelings.

680
00:52:02,910 --> 00:52:09,132
And I think we have to be very mindful of that when we have a process to look at the renaming.

681
00:52:09,832 --> 00:52:11,452
I'm not opposed to renaming.

682
00:52:11,533 --> 00:52:20,975
I'm not opposed to looking at things in retrospect, but what I am opposed to Mr. President is a process where people feel left out.

683
00:52:21,755 --> 00:52:25,657
And if one person feels left out, that's enough for me, Mr. President.

684
00:52:26,377 --> 00:52:30,558
And I'm respectfully asking that we ask our city solicitor

685
00:52:31,292 --> 00:52:41,319
I don't doubt for a second that the school committee has the authority to name a building, and I've told people that over the past year and a half, that they have the ability to name a building.

686
00:52:41,719 --> 00:52:59,150
All I'm asking is whether or not the Memphis City Council, through way of an ordinance, can create a policy, Mr. President, that includes the entire community when it comes to looking at municipal or school-owned buildings, and that we create

687
00:52:59,800 --> 00:53:18,594
a policy and procedure that ultimately has the goal of incorporating every comment, every person's wishes, and coming out with a process that we can all feel proud of at the end and not have the division that we're seeing right now, Mr. President.

688
00:53:18,614 --> 00:53:20,455
And that's all this is trying to accomplish.

689
00:53:20,856 --> 00:53:24,979
This is not trying to take away anyone's responsibilities, anyone's duties.

690
00:53:25,719 --> 00:53:26,980
It's seeing a concern.

691
00:53:27,821 --> 00:53:29,182
When I see a community divided,

692
00:53:29,794 --> 00:53:30,475
That concerns me.

693
00:53:30,495 --> 00:53:31,535
I've been around a lot of years.

694
00:53:32,336 --> 00:53:41,844
And when I see a community divided over an issue, we as legislators, the executive branch, I think have to step up and say, how do we better this process?

695
00:53:42,184 --> 00:53:48,670
How do we make it so we don't have to go through this every time we may decide that we want to rename something?

696
00:53:48,690 --> 00:53:56,316
And I feel that if this process continues in the manner it's going, all it's going to do is create division.

697
00:53:56,756 --> 00:53:58,658
And that would include on the municipal side.

698
00:53:59,446 --> 00:54:01,767
So I'm not saying this is strictly a school issue.

699
00:54:02,167 --> 00:54:03,488
It's on the municipal side as well.

700
00:54:03,508 --> 00:54:06,369
So I'm saying, open up the process to the entire community.

701
00:54:07,109 --> 00:54:08,870
And those are my comments, Mr. President.

702
00:54:08,890 --> 00:54:09,230
Thank you.

