963
01:16:23,470 --> 01:16:29,653
As many residents know, from time to time during municipal election season, the city holds preliminary elections.

964
01:16:30,378 --> 01:16:40,464
In recent years, I believe they have eliminated effectively one candidate out of a pool of 15 or 16 or two from 16 for city council.

965
01:16:40,884 --> 01:16:43,726
It's a very costly exercise.

966
01:16:43,766 --> 01:16:47,308
I believe it costs upwards of $50,000 of taxpayer money.

967
01:16:47,328 --> 01:16:54,913
And the outcome is really saying, well, you know, we're gonna have you pick from 14 candidates instead of 15 candidates.

968
01:16:55,617 --> 01:16:59,639
I think if that's the case, it may not be the best use of taxpayer dollars.

969
01:16:59,999 --> 01:17:04,762
I also think there's an argument that letting everybody run in the general election is a good thing.

970
01:17:04,782 --> 01:17:08,564
We're not eliminating one or two candidates from the outset.

971
01:17:09,244 --> 01:17:19,749
And I'm just interested into what my other fellow counselors think about potentially filing a home rule petition to cancel the preliminary election and just allow all candidates to run in the November general election.

972
01:17:20,590 --> 01:17:23,311
One other reason I bring this up is significant

973
01:17:24,198 --> 01:17:27,220
legislative uncertainty around the option of mail-in voting.

974
01:17:28,100 --> 01:17:38,887
It seems like the legislature may not pass a law by the time necessary to allow mail ballots for the preliminary election, but then may do it in time for the general election.

975
01:17:38,967 --> 01:17:41,628
So then we're talking about a different set of rules for each election.

976
01:17:42,229 --> 01:17:51,194
And I think it may just be better given the conditions that we're operating under to have the elections office focusing on making sure that the November election runs smoothly.

977
01:17:51,993 --> 01:17:53,674
Those are just some points for consideration.

978
01:17:53,694 --> 01:18:00,079
I'm interested into what my other fellow counselors think, and hopefully we can maybe take some action on it tonight.

979
01:18:00,359 --> 01:18:07,685
